%N A394386 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of ordered rooted trees with non-root node weights summing to n that have k non-root nodes; such that the root has weight 0, non-root nodes have positive integer weights, and only non-root nodes of odd weight can have branches.
%F A394386 G.f.: (-1 + x^2 + y*x^2 + (1 - x^2)*sqrt((1 - y*x^2/(1 - x^2))^2 - 4*y*x/(1 - x^2)))/(-2*y*x).
